        .row.margin-top-l
          .col-xs-12
            h3 Style
            p Use the following styles to determine importance of a button.
            ul
              li Default: Standard buttons
              li Primary: Provides extra visual weight and identifies the primary action in a set of buttons.
              li Accent: Give most importance to this buttons. Should be used very sparsely and only if you are 100% this is the most important button on the screen for the user. 
              li Success: Indicates a successful or positive action
              li Warning: Indicates caution should be taken with this action
              li Danger: Indicates a dangerous or potentially negative action
              li Flat button: Deemphasize a button by making it look like a link while maintaining button behavior
              
